{{!-- Legal Exposure Indicator — Methodology documentation page.
     Public, no-auth — renders ONLY static model documentation.
     View context: pageTitle, currentPath, user (no per-org/scan data). --}}

<div class="page-header">
  <h1>{{t "exposure.methodologyTitle"}}</h1>
</div>

{{!-- Disclaimer block --}}
<div class="alert alert--info" role="note" aria-labelledby="methodology-disclaimer-heading">
  <h2 id="methodology-disclaimer-heading" class="card__title">{{t "exposure.methodologyDisclaimerHeading"}}</h2>
  <p>{{t "exposure.methodologyDisclaimer"}}</p>
</div>

{{!-- Bands section --}}
<div class="card">
  <div class="card__header">
    <h2 class="card__title">Exposure Bands</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="card__body">
    <p class="text-muted">The indicator assigns one of four ordinal bands. No numeric score or percentage is produced — the band is the only verdict.</p>
    <table class="data-table" aria-label="Exposure band definitions">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Band</th>
          <th scope="col">Meaning</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="rpt-badge rpt-badge--notice-light">{{t "exposure.band.lower"}}</span></td>
          <td>No high-exposure jurisdiction drivers detected and finding pressure is zero. No immediate action indicated by the model.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="rpt-badge rpt-badge--warning-light">{{t "exposure.band.moderate"}}</span></td>
          <td>Low finding pressure (severity-weighted score &gt; 0 and &lt; 15) with no high-exposure jurisdiction drivers. Some attention recommended.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="rpt-badge rpt-badge--error-light">{{t "exposure.band.elevated"}}</span></td>
          <td>Moderate finding pressure (score 15–39) or the site serves jurisdictions with notable web-accessibility filing activity (e.g. California / Unruh Act). Prompt remediation recommended.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="rpt-badge rpt-badge--error-light">{{t "exposure.band.high"}}</span></td>
          <td>High finding pressure (severity-weighted score ≥ 40) or the site serves high-filing jurisdictions (EU/EAA, New York, Florida, Illinois) or an ADA Title II deadline has expired. Immediate remediation recommended.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>

{{!-- Inputs section --}}
<div class="card">
  <div class="card__header">
    <h2 class="card__title">Model Inputs</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="card__body">

    <h3 class="card__title">Severity-weighted finding pressure</h3>
    <p class="text-muted">Open findings from the scan are assigned weights and summed to produce a pressure score. The weights reflect the relative certainty and severity of each finding type:</p>
    <table class="data-table" aria-label="Finding severity weights">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Finding type</th>
          <th scope="col">Weight</th>
          <th scope="col">Rationale</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Confirmed violations</td>
          <td>× 10</td>
          <td>Mandatory failures manually verified — highest weight</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Errors</td>
          <td>× 3</td>
          <td>Automated scan errors — high confidence</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Warnings</td>
          <td>× 1</td>
          <td>Potential issues requiring review</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Notices</td>
          <td>× 0.1</td>
          <td>Informational — low weight</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3 class="card__title" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Pressure score thresholds</h3>
    <table class="data-table" aria-label="Finding pressure score to band mapping">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Pressure score</th>
          <th scope="col">Band contribution</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>0</td><td>Lower</td></tr>
        <tr><td>&gt; 0 and &lt; 15</td><td>Moderate</td></tr>
        <tr><td>15 to 39 (inclusive)</td><td>Elevated</td></tr>
        <tr><td>≥ 40</td><td>High</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3 class="card__title" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Jurisdiction applicability</h3>
    <p class="text-muted">When a site's selected jurisdictions or regulations match a high-exposure entry, a band contribution is added. The final band is the higher of the jurisdiction contribution and the finding-pressure contribution.</p>
    <table class="data-table" aria-label="Jurisdiction drivers and band contributions">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Jurisdiction / Regulation</th>
          <th scope="col">Band contribution</th>
          <th scope="col">Basis</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>EU / European Accessibility Act (EU-EAA)</td>
          <td>High</td>
          <td>Directive (EU) 2019/882 — in effect 28 Jun 2025</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>New York (US-NY)</td>
          <td>High</td>
          <td>Highest US ADA web-accessibility filing volume (coarse classification)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Florida (US-FL)</td>
          <td>High</td>
          <td>Second-highest US ADA web-accessibility filing volume (coarse classification)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Illinois (US-IL)</td>
          <td>High</td>
          <td>IITAA + notable ADA plaintiff activity (coarse classification)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>California (US-CA)</td>
          <td>Elevated</td>
          <td>Unruh Act + ADA overlap; elevated filing activity (coarse classification)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3 class="card__title" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">ADA Title II countdown</h3>
    <p class="text-muted">When ADA Title II is in the site's selected regulations, the conservative baseline deadline (large entity, soonest applicable) is used because entity size is not known at the site level. The deadline is shown as a driver regardless of its effect on the band.</p>
    <table class="data-table" aria-label="ADA Title II deadline tiers">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Entity tier</th>
          <th scope="col">Deadline</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Large (population ≥ 50,000 or budget ≥ $100 M)</td>
          <td>24 Apr 2026</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Mid-size (population 10,000–49,999)</td>
          <td>26 Apr 2027</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Small (population &lt; 10,000 / special district)</td>
          <td>26 Apr 2028</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Unknown / conservative baseline (used by this model)</td>
          <td>24 Apr 2026 (earliest)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>

{{!-- Data sources section --}}
<div class="card">
  <div class="card__header">
    <h2 class="card__title">Data Sources</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="card__body">
    <table class="data-table" aria-label="Static data sources used by the model">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Source</th>
          <th scope="col">Entry in effect</th>
          <th scope="col">Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>EU Accessibility Act — Directive (EU) 2019/882</td>
          <td>28 Jun 2025</td>
          <td>Full enforcement for covered services</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>ADA Title II — 89 Fed. Reg. 31320 (Apr 24 2024)</td>
          <td>Large entities: 24 Apr 2026</td>
          <td>Conservative baseline — large entity deadline used when entity size unknown</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>High-filing jurisdiction classification</td>
          <td>Data as of 2026-06-07</td>
          <td>Coarse classification based on publicly available ADA web-accessibility filing patterns (NY, FL, IL). Not a precise litigation count; intended as a conservative transparency indicator only.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>

{{!-- Data as of section --}}
<div class="card">
  <div class="card__header">
    <h2 class="card__title">Data As Of</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="card__body">
    <p>The static data tables in this model were last reviewed on <strong>2026-06-07</strong>. Regulatory deadlines and filing-pattern classifications are updated when material changes occur. The asOf date on each exposure indicator reflects the date the underlying model constants were last reviewed.</p>
  </div>
</div>

